article.headline: Towson 99, James Madison 84
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Gary Neal scored 40 points and Lawrence Hamm led a 12-0 run midway through the second half as hot-shooting Towson defeated James Madison 99-84 Saturday night. The Tigers (6-7, 2-2 Colonial Athletic Association) shot 63 percent from the field. Neal was 13-of-21 and Hamm, who scored 29 points, was 12-of-14. Towson led 46-45 at the break, and the teams traded baskets for the first eight minutes of the second half. James Madison (3-9, 0-4) took a 63-62 lead on Ray Barbosa's 3-pointer with 11:32 left, but Neal hit a 3 to start a 12-0 run that included a dunk and a three-point play by Hamm. Another Barbosa 3 cut the Tigers' lead to 78-71 with 6:29 left, but the Dukes could get no closer as Neal hit a jumper and a pair of free throws during a 10-0 run over the next three minutes. Barbosa scored 28 points on 10-of-21 shooting. Juwann James added 19 and Daniel Freeman 14 for the Dukes, who shot only 44 percent and were outscored 24-9 from the free-throw line. Dennard Abraham added 11 points for Towson.
